<br>
They often don't want to upgrade our nukes because of wizards or give us stronger pets because of melees, so they think up something new and fitting, and then nerf it when it proves too powerful. Mod Rod 2 and COH are prime examples.<br>
<br>
Heck,I even remember back in the old days when we didn't have a mod rod spell or a dual wielding pet. It took some time for magi to obtain even ground with other classes.<br>
<br>
And it has taken awhile for VI to balance out magi without @#%$ off the other classes. Even the necromancer is not as difficult to balance as the mage class because their abilities differ so greatly from other classes.<br>
<br>
To this day, I still have no clue what VI intended us to do in the overall scheme of things. I don't know if they intended us to be damage dealers or a summoning support class or a solo class or what not. <br>
<br>
We are the only class that can do three really good forms of damage: Direct Damage with nukes, Melee damage with pets, and indirect unresistable damage with damage shields and we even have a few DOTs to boot. More than anything else this made me believe the mage was designed to deal damage.<br>
<br>
Let's face it, magi have been the &quot;odd class out&quot; at VI for all the time I have played EQ. We are a strange class. I believe magicians are probably the most misunderstood class in this game.The only class that was more misunderstood at certain points in time were bards, but now everyone loves bards and understands that they boost the group. <br>
<br>
Magicians are a strange class that has made class balancing for VI very difficult. If there were not so many mage players who loved the class and were adamant about receiving upgrades and fixes, the mage class would have died long ago.<br>
<br>
The magician eq experience is different from any other class. It can be rewarding, but it can also be exceedingly frustrating. Though I enjoyed playing a mage, I really wish VI would have put more thought into the class.<br>
<br>
At least it sounds like PoP was a great upgrade for magi because SOL was &quot;the suck&quot; for magicians. I just hope those magi who have stuck it out can enjoy the last remaining days of EQ. <p>Natharius Bladestorm<br>
Lvl 55 Mage<br>
Saryrn<br>
Isengard<br>
